cc:Work.dc:title: Earth and North Star
cc:Work.dc:description: This picture shows why the North Star doesn't seem to move as the earth spins. (All other stars do.) I hope it will be useful for someone. I created the original image in Corel Draw for a self-published book on the constellations. I used Inkscape to color and shade it.
